28:07.436 --> 28:10.147
I'm just happy you're coming home.

28:10.898 --> 28:14.067
I can make those grilled cheese sandwiches
you like, with the crust cut off.

28:14.151 --> 28:17.279
I'm an adult. I eat crusts now.

28:17.362 --> 28:20.866
Of course, you do, sweetie.

28:29.707 --> 28:31.709
-Where are we? What is this place?
-Uh-oh.

28:31.793 --> 28:35.505
I smell cigarettes and burnt coffee.
You know what that means.

28:36.882 --> 28:37.799
Alcoholics.

28:39.384 --> 28:41.762
But Greg's not an alcoholic.

28:43.847 --> 28:44.848
I drink anywhere.

28:44.932 --> 28:46.475
Tacos and tequila.

28:46.558 --> 28:48.602
But I do my study drinking here.

28:48.685 --> 28:51.063
We're way too sober for this wedding.
How about I get us some shots?

28:51.146 --> 28:53.607
Ooh, I don't leave
when there's whiskey left.

28:53.690 --> 28:58.654
-I need to take a nap.
-Oh, yes, the classic Serrano pass out.

28:58.737 --> 29:00.322
Oh...

29:00.405 --> 29:03.450
-Yeah, I called that one.
-Look, there he is. There he is.

29:04.284 --> 29:07.871
-Hi, I'm Greg.
-Oh, shh, shh! He's gonna say something.

29:07.955 --> 29:11.250
So, I'm here because one night,

29:11.333 --> 29:15.879
I had ten cocktails at a wedding,
as one does.

29:15.963 --> 29:21.093
And then, I passed out
in my own vomit, as one does.

29:21.843 --> 29:25.013
The next morning,
I got in my car and a cop stopped me,

29:25.097 --> 29:26.723
as they do when you're weaving.

29:26.807 --> 29:28.058
And, um...

29:29.476 --> 29:32.479
It turns out I was still legally drunk
from the night before,

29:32.562 --> 29:37.442
and I got arrested, as again, one does.

29:37.526 --> 29:38.360
Um...

29:39.278 --> 29:43.198
The judge sentenced me to come here
every day for a month.

29:44.700 --> 29:48.120
[sighs] My plan was to knock out
these meetings, get my court card signed,

29:48.203 --> 29:51.873
and go back to being as angry as I could
with just about anyone I could think of.

29:51.957 --> 29:57.170
My mom, my dad, my job, West Covina,
men who wear skinny jeans.

29:57.254 --> 29:58.964
-[man] Yeah!
-Thank you, Frank.

29:59.840 --> 30:03.302
But that whole time, there was
one person I was really angry at.

30:03.385 --> 30:05.178
That's me. It's me. He's talking about me.

30:06.346 --> 30:08.307
-Myself.
-Oh, it's him. It's him.

30:08.390 --> 30:09.850
-That's better. It's him.
-Yeah, way better.

30:09.933 --> 30:12.019
I'm responsible
for not only what happened that night,

30:12.102 --> 30:15.647
but for the whole mess that was my life
up to that night.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.275
And now, I see...

30:19.818 --> 30:22.321
I needed to face something
that I'd always known...

30:24.323 --> 30:25.907
That I'm an alcoholic.

30:27.951 --> 30:29.661
And I've known that
since I had my first drink.

30:29.745 --> 30:34.875
My first sip felt like-- I don't know--
like glitter was exploding inside of me.

30:34.958 --> 30:38.045
[sighs, clears throat]

30:38.128 --> 30:39.629
That's how alcohol affects me.

30:40.714 --> 30:43.008
So, here I am, facing that reality.

30:43.091 --> 30:47.929
And now that I have, the funny thing is,
I'm not as angry anymore...

30:48.013 --> 30:51.516
at anyone, really, including myself.

30:51.600 --> 30:54.436
I mean, the guys who still wear
the skinny jeans-- I mean, enough already.

30:54.519 --> 30:55.896
-[Frank] Yeah!
-Yeah. Amen, Frank.

30:55.979 --> 30:57.147
Um...

30:57.230 --> 30:58.440
Anyway, thank you all for listening,

30:58.523 --> 31:01.651
and thanks for putting up with me
over these past few weeks,

31:01.735 --> 31:04.279
when I just thought
you were a bunch of sad losers.

31:04.363 --> 31:07.032
But now, I know that I am...
uh, we're not...

31:07.115 --> 31:11.828
You know what I'm saying. Also,
I'm so sorry for the glitter metaphor. I don't know where that came from,
uh, but it felt right, so...

31:20.462 --> 31:25.509
So, is now a bad time
to tell him about Josh?

31:30.472 --> 31:32.099
-Mm-mm-mm.
-Really?

31:34.226 --> 31:38.438
God, I felt so bad
at that meeting tonight.

31:38.522 --> 31:40.357
Yeah, tough break for Greg.

31:40.440 --> 31:43.235
[scoffs] I don't care about that guy.
I always knew he was a boozer.

31:43.318 --> 31:45.654
No, I feel bad
because I realized something. That glitter feeling, I know that feeling.

31:48.156 --> 31:52.411
I feel it every time I do those bad things
to help Rebecca.

31:55.789 --> 31:57.499
It's like my drug.

31:57.582 --> 32:01.753
It's like I swear it off, and then,
tonight, she just pulls me back in.

32:01.837 --> 32:04.464
It's like I did another fistful of blow.

32:04.548 --> 32:06.842
I'm addicted to her life.

32:06.925 --> 32:10.178
It's like the high I get
from those vampire novels,

32:10.262 --> 32:14.433
or <i>The Bachelor, </i>or when I write
a really great legal brief at work.

32:14.516 --> 32:15.851
Why don't you do more of those?

32:15.934 --> 32:18.770
Fill the void with something
you're good at and like.

32:18.854 --> 32:20.439
Write more briefs or something.

32:20.522 --> 32:24.025
Well... [scoffs] I mean,
that's not how it works, Scott.

32:24.109 --> 32:28.321
I mean, I can't just, you know, go around
writing random legal papers for fun.

32:28.405 --> 32:29.364
All right.

32:31.158 --> 32:32.451
You'll figure something out.

32:37.247 --> 32:38.498
[Rebecca]
<i>Paula.</i>

32:38.582 --> 32:40.959
<i>Paula, come back to me. I need you.</i>

32:41.042 --> 32:44.337
I don't know what to do. I can't tell Greg
about me and Josh because--

32:44.421 --> 32:47.257
Poor guy, that's the last thing he needs.
He'll probably start drinking again.

32:47.340 --> 32:50.510
But I was thinking, what if there's a way
for Greg to find out about me and Josh

32:50.594 --> 32:52.471
without me being the bad guy
and having to tell him?

32:52.554 --> 32:54.973
-Rebecca--
-Wait, wait, wait! Wait, wait, wait!

32:55.056 --> 32:57.017
So, I have an idea. This is the bad pitch.

32:57.100 --> 32:59.394
Something like this.
It's fine. Don't worry about it.

32:59.478 --> 33:02.731
So, we arrange somehow,
maybe through the radio,

33:02.814 --> 33:04.441
for Josh and Greg to win a sweepstakes.

33:04.524 --> 33:06.735
Maybe they win, like, $10,000
and a trip to Belize.

33:06.818 --> 33:08.069
So, they're on the beach,

33:08.153 --> 33:10.530
and a skywriter plane flies over them,

33:10.614 --> 33:12.407
and it spells out
"Josh and Rebecca are in love."

33:12.491 --> 33:14.618
Now, by this point--
let's say it's, like, 10 days in--

33:14.701 --> 33:16.286
Josh and Greg are in great moods.

33:16.369 --> 33:19.247
They've been playing with monkeys,
going to cat hotels, drinking mai tais--

33:19.331 --> 33:21.416
-Greg can't drink mai tais.
-Drinking virgin mai tais.

33:21.500 --> 33:24.544
And Greg is gonna see the banner,
with tears in his eyes, turn to Josh,

33:24.628 --> 33:25.879
and say, "Oh, my gosh.

33:25.962 --> 33:28.715
I suddenly know your truth
and you know mine. Embrace me, brother."

33:28.798 --> 33:31.134
Now, as they're hugging,
I come down on a parachute and I go,

33:31.218 --> 33:35.055
"What are you guys doing here?
Did you win a contest? I won a contest."

33:35.138 --> 33:37.307
First draft, all thoughts are welcome.

33:38.433 --> 33:40.977
Perfect. Do it.

33:43.730 --> 33:45.106
No, you're joking. What?

33:46.399 --> 33:49.778
I've given this a lot of thought
and I have made a decision.

33:51.947 --> 33:54.658
I can give advice and I can listen,

33:54.741 --> 33:57.911
but I cannot do any more immoral
or illegal things.

33:57.994 --> 34:00.247
No more schemes. It is not good for me.

34:00.330 --> 34:04.793
And if you are really my friend,
then you will accept it.

34:04.876 --> 34:06.294
Wow. Um...

34:07.879 --> 34:08.922
Okay.

34:10.715 --> 34:11.883
So, you agree?

34:11.967 --> 34:13.301
Uh...

34:13.385 --> 34:14.928
Yeah. I mean, I guess, I agree.

34:15.887 --> 34:19.808
Great! Okay, uh, I just need you
to sign something.

34:19.891 --> 34:21.643
-Mrs. H.?
-Oh, hello.

34:22.894 --> 34:23.853
-What's this?
-Okay.

34:23.937 --> 34:27.232
This is just a simple contract
laying out the terms of our friendship.

34:27.315 --> 34:30.402
It stipulates that my services as a friend
are limited to consultation and support,

34:30.485 --> 34:31.486
and excludes shenanigans.

34:31.570 --> 34:35.156
So, you just need to sign
here, here, and here.

34:35.240 --> 34:37.867
Initial there, there, and there.

34:38.827 --> 34:41.705
Paula, this isn't fair. This is not
what best friends do to each other.

34:41.788 --> 34:45.917
They don't make each other sign
legally binding contracts.

34:46.001 --> 34:47.043
Do you not trust me?

34:47.877 --> 34:49.462
Honey, of course, I trust you.

34:49.546 --> 34:50.505
[scoffs]

34:51.923 --> 34:53.383
I don't trust myself.

35:05.020 --> 35:08.607
-Wow, this is really well done.
-I did it myself. You like it?

35:08.690 --> 35:12.611
I mean, no, I hate it,
but, Paula, it's excellent work.

35:14.821 --> 35:16.698
Are you sure you want me to sign this?

35:20.243 --> 35:21.119
[sighs]

35:21.661 --> 35:22.704
For the friendship.

35:29.419 --> 35:30.629
Ooh.

35:34.382 --> 35:35.342
Thank you.

35:46.019 --> 35:49.022
Dude, you are gonna love
living with your parents.

35:49.105 --> 35:51.566
I mean, everyone says the best part
is the laundry,

35:51.650 --> 35:52.859
but I don't care about that.

35:52.942 --> 35:56.988
Real talk? If I have a nightmare,
I don't have to tough it out.

35:57.072 --> 35:59.491
-You hear what I'm saying?
-Sounds great.

36:00.659 --> 36:01.868
You're doing the right thing, man.

36:01.951 --> 36:04.746
And maybe one of these nights,
we can both take our moms out.

36:04.829 --> 36:06.539
Double date.

36:16.257 --> 36:17.676
[takes deep breath]

36:19.844 --> 36:22.847
["The Entertainer" playing]

36:22.931 --> 36:27.018
<i>♪ When your fella</i>
<i>no longer wants a drawer ♪</i>

36:27.102 --> 36:30.855
<i>♪ And you don't want to hurt</i>
<i>your alcoholic friend ♪</i>

36:30.939 --> 36:34.484
<i>♪ God, it's so hard to sing a sad song ♪</i>

36:34.567 --> 36:38.196
<i>♪ With a melody</i>
<i>that makes you want to Charleston ♪</i>

36:40.490 --> 36:41.449
[door bell rings]

36:47.706 --> 36:48.540
Hi.

36:52.502 --> 36:54.003
Uh, what are you doing here?

36:54.838 --> 36:57.465
I am looking for those socks.

36:58.800 --> 37:01.886
They're pricey--
The ones that wick moisture.

37:02.971 --> 37:05.598
Right. Right! 'Cause your feet are sweaty.

37:05.682 --> 37:08.768
-[laughs] Yeah.
-Um, yeah. Let's look for them.

37:09.936 --> 37:11.229
Right, right.

37:12.439 --> 37:14.149
Actually, I'm really glad you're here.

37:14.232 --> 37:16.901
I've been wanting to talk to you
about something.

37:16.985 --> 37:19.070
-About socks?
-No.

37:19.154 --> 37:20.572
Um...

37:22.031 --> 37:24.117
I think you were right
about the Greg thing.

37:24.200 --> 37:30.999
It's just-- I have this, um, intuition
that he's not in a good place right now.

37:32.000 --> 37:33.501
So, I agree with you.

37:33.585 --> 37:36.421
You're very smart and wise, as usual.

37:36.504 --> 37:37.422
[chuckles]

37:39.174 --> 37:41.676
Until we make things okay with Greg,

37:41.760 --> 37:45.388
I do not think we should interact
in a romantic way.

37:46.598 --> 37:49.893
Oh, God. I am so glad I came over,
and we are on the same page. I feel the exact same way.
I'm so relieved.

37:54.105 --> 37:57.233
I mean, this is the best
I've felt in a long time.

37:57.317 --> 38:00.361
Yeah. I'm glad
that we're practicing self-control.

38:00.445 --> 38:02.030
Me, too. We're super mature.

38:02.363 --> 38:04.741
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

38:04.824 --> 38:09.537
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

38:09.621 --> 38:11.498
[sensual music playing]

38:16.753 --> 38:19.255
<i>♪ We should definitely</i>
<i>not have sex right now ♪</i>

38:19.339 --> 38:22.175
<i>♪ We should definitely</i>
<i>not have sex right now ♪</i>

38:22.258 --> 38:25.804
<i>♪ It would complicate the situation ♪</i>

38:26.805 --> 38:29.390
<i>♪ It's the adult thing</i>
<i>to not have sex right now ♪</i>

38:29.474 --> 38:31.851
<i>♪ We have the common sense</i>
<i>not to have sex right now ♪</i>

38:31.935 --> 38:33.520
<i>♪ I need time to reflect ♪</i>

38:33.603 --> 38:36.147
<i>♪ And I'm in a really weird place ♪</i>

38:41.820 --> 38:44.739
<i>♪ It feels so good</i>
<i>to be having sex right now ♪</i>

38:44.823 --> 38:47.367
<i>♪ So good to be having sex right now ♪</i>

38:47.450 --> 38:52.455
<i>♪ What makes it so good is we just said</i>
<i>we shouldn't be having sex right now ♪</i>

38:52.539 --> 38:55.041
<i>♪ But now we can't stop</i>
<i>having sex right now ♪</i>

38:55.124 --> 38:57.877
<i>♪ I mean, it would be weirder</i>
<i>to stop having sex ♪</i>

38:57.961 --> 39:01.840
<i>♪ Such a good point,</i>
<i>we might as well just finish ♪</i>

39:13.059 --> 39:15.311
<i>♪ We should definitely</i>
<i>not have sex again ♪</i>

39:15.395 --> 39:18.273
<i>♪ We should definitely</i>
<i>not have sex again ♪</i>

39:18.356 --> 39:22.402
<i>♪ What are we, bonobos in a tree? ♪</i>

39:22.485 --> 39:28.157
<i>♪ There's no reason to have sex again,</i>
<i>but I'll be ready to go again in ten ♪</i>

39:28.241 --> 39:30.869
<i>♪ What if we say</i>
<i>this is the last sex night? ♪</i>

39:30.952 --> 39:33.538
<i>♪ It's like in movies</i>
<i>when robbers do one last heist ♪</i>

39:33.621 --> 39:35.999
<i>♪ This night will be our last sex heist ♪</i>

39:36.082 --> 39:41.462
<i>♪ But then again,</i>
<i>those movies always get a sequel ♪</i>

39:41.546 --> 39:42.672
[music fades out]

39:44.507 --> 39:46.426
-Yeah, I don't--
-I don't-- Is it--?

39:46.509 --> 39:48.136
[both moaning]

40:22.211 --> 40:24.380
-Is it real?
-Oh, yeah.

40:24.464 --> 40:25.882
-Yeah.
-Yeah. It's one of the things--

40:25.965 --> 40:28.968
-What do you think it is?
-Those? Salt and pepper.

40:29.052 --> 40:31.679
I think that one of those is salt
and one of those is pepper.

40:31.763 --> 40:35.808
That would be my guess. I don't know why
you have that with your clothes, but...

40:35.892 --> 40:39.479
What is the--?
What are we supposed to do about...?

40:40.355 --> 40:41.564
-This?
-Yeah, this.

41:24.482 --> 41:25.775
[man]
And cut!

41:25.858 --> 41:29.487
Great job, everyone!
So good. Great take.

41:29.570 --> 41:32.532
So, what's this for again?
Is it for TV? Film?

41:32.615 --> 41:35.910
-Oh, no, no, this is just in my head.
-What do you mean, in your head?

41:35.994 --> 41:38.121
This is all fake. Yeah, this is, um--

41:38.204 --> 41:40.748
It's like an emotional
thesis statement for myself.

41:40.832 --> 41:42.583
None of you exist.

41:42.667 --> 41:45.795
But that can't be true.
I have feelings, I have memories.

41:45.878 --> 41:48.339
No, you don't.
I just have an active fantasy life.

41:48.423 --> 41:51.968
I created you and I can destroy you.
Okay, let's run it again.

41:52.051 --> 41:53.469
Do I exist?

41:55.555 --> 41:56.639
Anyone else have any questions?

41:56.723 --> 41:58.224
Okay, from the top.
